1. After downloading the zip file, click on it to get the folder and put it on your desktop.
2. Open your terminal and write "cd /Users/insert your name here/Desktop/CARLoS-Agents-main" and then press enter. If you want to copy it yourself, right-click on anything inside the main folder and copy the part that starts with 'Where:'.
3. Write "source rl_env/Scripts/activate" in the terminal and press enter.
4. Write "pip3 install -r requirements.txt" in the terminal and press enter.
5. Write "python3 -m rlagent.test_env" in the terminal and press enter. If the terminal is on full screen, exit it because then you may not see the simulation.
Now you should see logs in the terminal and a simulation window open.
